1
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:18,893
Umemiya.

2
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:22,480
We've got a problem.

3
00:00:24,232 --> 00:00:26,109
Yeah, I know.

4
00:00:28,319 --> 00:00:29,863
<i>He already knew?</i>

5
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,198
<i>Just who in the world...</i>

6
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:35,827
We don't have enough seedlings!

7
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:39,622
We've got one extra planting spot left.

8
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,541
Is there anything you wanna eat?

9
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:43,585
Not that. I'm talking about Shishito...

10
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:47,088
Shishito peppers? But you got
a weak stomach! Sure you can eat that?

11
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:50,258
They're not on the same page...

12
00:00:50,341 --> 00:00:54,345
<i>I see. So that's where Hiragi-san
got his stomachaches.</i>

13
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:58,725
That is... Umemiya?

14
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:03,438
You mean "that man" is <i>Umemiya-san!</i>

15
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:04,439
Shut up!

16
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:09,527
Oh? What brings you all here?

17
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:12,030
Hey!

18
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:14,532
This one is a tomato plant.

19
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:16,117
This one's a green pepper.

20
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:18,578
Then we've got eggplants,
cucumbers, and okra!

21
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:22,290
They're all unique and cute!

22
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:27,587
It's all right.

23
00:01:30,215 --> 00:01:33,802
For Pete's sake.
He never listens to other people

24
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:37,096
and once he opens his mouth,
he never shuts up.

25
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:38,807
Goddammit.

26
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:40,975
They're all just some grass, aren't they?

27
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:45,480
What? Look closer!
They're all so different!

28
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:48,066
<i>Though, still...</i>

29
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:50,735
<i>He was acting like this during
the announcement, too.</i>

30
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,695
<i>It's like he loves to goof around.</i>

31
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:57,075
<i>But he was able to change
the atmosphere with just his voice.</i>

32
00:01:57,158 --> 00:02:00,120
I hope we'll get lots of veggies
from this little guy.

33
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:03,665
<i>Just what makes people flock to him?</i>

34
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:13,049
Please... allow me... to explain myself!

35
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:16,219
<i>It must be hard for him
to just stay quiet in this situation.</i>

36
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:20,140
I saw a shoplifter
in the shopping district.

37
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:24,519
So I went after him, but before I knew it,
I was already in Shishitoren's turf.

38
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:28,606
And when they started chasing after me.
I thought I was done for...

39
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,860
But these two saved me!

40
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:36,114
I looked up to Bofurin,
and got ahead of myself...

41
00:02:36,197 --> 00:02:40,869
But in the end, I sparked
a fight with Shishitoren...

42
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:44,497
I'm so sorry!

43
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:49,544
Sasaki.

44
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:53,673
How... do you know my name?

45
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:55,717
Thanks, man.

46
00:02:58,636 --> 00:03:00,930
You said you sparked a fight with them,

47
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:04,976
but that was only because you wanted
to protect the town and its people, right?

48
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:07,520
Then you don't have to
apologize for anything!

49
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:08,688
Just leave the rest...

50
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:14,068
to your big brothers here!

51
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:17,822
So?

52
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:20,783
How did these guys save you?

53
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,578
They kicked the other guy into orbit.

54
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:25,622
They kicked him into orbit?

55
00:03:28,207 --> 00:03:31,294
Man, I pity that other guy!

56
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,880
It's no use talking anything
through with them.

57
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:36,591
I see. They kicked them into orbit, huh?

58
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:41,012
I was there, but I couldn't stop them.
I'm sorry.

59
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:44,724
There you go again, always trying
to shoulder the blame all by yourself.

60
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:47,977
I was the one who asked you
to look after them.

61
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:50,313
See? Your stomach's acting up again.

62
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:54,275
But it was all Sakura-san's fault
for pushing the guy's buttons.

63
00:03:54,359 --> 00:03:56,903
Shut up already!
Keep your comments to yourself!

64
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:59,364
What? You picked a fight with them?

65
00:03:59,447 --> 00:04:03,243
Those punks call themselves
the devotees of power and all,

66
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:06,579
but get off on beating up a weakling!
It's so lame, so I said it...

67
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:08,665
to them...

68
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:11,584
You said it?

69
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,880
I see, I see.

70
00:04:18,883 --> 00:04:20,802
Well said!

71
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:25,890
Me too. I think
they've been pretty lame lately.

72
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:29,394
Sakura, I heard what you did
on the main street yesterday.

73
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:32,647
And you saved Sasaki today.

74
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:35,608
Thank you for protecting my family.

75
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:39,153
I'm happy to see we got ourselves
another reliable little brother!

76
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:47,120
<i>What... is this hot feeling
I feel up to the tips of my ears?</i>

77
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:50,540
<i>I feel so relaxed, it kinda pisses me off.</i>

78
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:56,045
<i>I feel like I somewhat understand
why they're all so attached to him now.</i>

79
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,799
<i>They must feel safe with him.</i>

80
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:04,012
Why are you treating me
like your little brother?

81
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:08,891
I consider everyone in this town
as family.

82
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:15,648
Kaji? What's up?

83
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:19,110
<i>Shishi... toren...</i>

84
00:05:19,193 --> 00:05:21,821
Hey, Kaji? Kaji? What's wrong?

85
00:05:21,904 --> 00:05:24,073
What is it? Is something happening?

86
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,200
Hello!

87
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,500
Helloo! Helloo! Helloo!

88
00:05:35,501 --> 00:05:37,962
HELLOOOOOOOO!

89
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:43,468
I am the leader of Shishitoren!

90
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:45,636
Choji Tomiyama.

91
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:49,974
Ume-chan!

92
00:05:50,058 --> 00:05:51,934
I'm here to challenge you...

93
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:55,521
to a fight! Fight! Fight!

94
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:32,452
The leader? Why is the leader here?

95
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:34,537
For revenge? For war?

96
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:39,750
<i>Shishitoren's second-in-command,
Jo Togame!</i>

97
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,878
<i>That means...</i>

98
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:44,255
<i>he's stronger than that guy!</i>

99
00:07:51,095 --> 00:07:52,722
<i>What was that just now?</i>

100
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:55,725
Huh? Sakura-san?

101
00:07:58,186 --> 00:08:00,605
Suo-san! Sugishita-san!

102
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:02,690
Sasaki-kun? You too?

103
00:08:03,107 --> 00:08:05,776
Wait for me!

104
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:11,782
You guys stay here.

105
00:08:11,866 --> 00:08:14,577
Not a chance! Let me fight!

106
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,580
Don't make me repeat myself.

107
00:08:19,707 --> 00:08:20,958
<i>Crap...</i>

108
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:24,128
<i>I can't make my legs take another step...</i>

109
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:26,422
<i>He's acting nothing like before!</i>

110
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:29,133
<i>Is it really the same guy?</i>

111
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:33,304
Hey, Tomiyama.

112
00:08:33,387 --> 00:08:35,223
Look what you've got there.

113
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,891
That belongs to us.

114
00:08:36,974 --> 00:08:39,310
Yeah, I know.

115
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:41,562
You mad? You mad?

116
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:44,065
You seem happy.

117
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:50,112
<i>He's facing that Umemiya up close,
but still smiling.</i>

118
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:51,697
<i>What kind of monster is he?</i>

119
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:54,158
All right, Ume-chan!

120
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,703
Fight! Fight!

121
00:08:59,121 --> 00:09:01,999
You're the one who struck us first!

122
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:05,211
That's a good enough reason
to brawl it out, right?

123
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:10,216
Fight me! Fight me!

124
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:12,969
-Fight me! Fight me!
<i>-This guy just won't shut up.</i>

125
00:09:13,052 --> 00:09:16,264
You're right. We're the ones
who struck you guys first.

126
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,979
But... you mowed down
a ton of our guys, too.

127
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:25,189
You've got your fill now, haven't you?

128
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:26,607
Now we're even.

129
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,070
You're right.

130
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:33,906
Is... Is he satisfied, then?

131
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:37,702
Now, turn around and go ba...

132
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:47,336
Sheesh, you're just as impatient as ever.

133
00:09:52,216 --> 00:09:54,969
C'mon, Ume-chan! I just struck you!

134
00:09:55,052 --> 00:09:56,387
Now's your turn!

135
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:58,639
Come on! You gotta pay me back, right?

136
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:02,101
Why do you want to fight that badly?

137
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:06,564
Rather than fighting...

138
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:09,817
I want you, Ume-chan.

139
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:18,909
It's been somewhat boring
since I made my way to the top.

140
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:21,454
<i>But even though you're also at the top,</i>

141
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:24,206
<i>you're always smiling like
you're having fun.</i>

142
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,460
That's unfair.

143
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:33,924
That's why I'm going to take
all of Furin and you, for myself!

144
00:10:37,053 --> 00:10:39,597
That's just ridiculous.

145
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:42,975
I see.

146
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:47,355
You've got it hard, huh, Tomiyama?

147
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:51,150
Hey, hey!

148
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:55,571
What kind of silly bullcrap
are you feeding our general here?

149
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:58,449
Huh? Why are you all here?

150
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:01,869
You see...

151
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:05,122
If we let our general go raiding
enemies on his own...

152
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:09,710
it won't look good on us, okay?

153
00:11:09,794 --> 00:11:11,420
Sheesh.

154
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:15,508
You rushed out right the moment
I told you what happened.

155
00:11:15,591 --> 00:11:18,928
I've always said you gotta wait
until someone finishes talking...

156
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:21,097
Hello, Othello-kun.

157
00:11:21,972 --> 00:11:23,724
Short time no see.

158
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:25,810
Yo, scraggly.

159
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:27,603
Hey, I told you guys to sta...

160
00:11:27,686 --> 00:11:28,604
Shut up!

161
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:31,190
I won't get in your way
if it's one-on-one.

162
00:11:31,273 --> 00:11:34,110
But I don't like people
ganging up on one guy!

163
00:11:35,277 --> 00:11:40,658
I'm gonna fight him one-on-one,
so all of you need to back off!

164
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:46,372
I think it'll be a bit difficult
to do that now.

165
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:48,457
Take a look around.

166
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:57,591
Wha... This is getting out of hand!

167
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:02,555
All of you, don't you dare come down here!

168
00:12:05,641 --> 00:12:06,934
Tomiyama.

169
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:09,562
I'll take you on, one-on-one.

170
00:12:09,645 --> 00:12:12,064
Tell your men to step back.

171
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:15,776
Got it! I just wanna fight you, anyway!

172
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,027
Oh, come on.

173
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:20,573
Your general sure is a softy.

174
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:22,741
Or is he just scared?

175
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:24,493
Hey. Shut up or I'll crush you!

176
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:27,580
Don't get pissy just 'cause I'm right.

177
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:30,458
Hey, wasn't that
one of the kids from earlier?

178
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,585
Oh, I knew it!

179
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:36,630
They're so plain, but I could tell
right away! I'm good, aren't I?

180
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:40,676
You've got one craggy-looking face,
but you talk like a little boy.

181
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:41,969
How cute.

182
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:43,721
You say what?

183
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:48,225
There, there. Calm down, guys.

184
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:49,810
Hey, Choji.

185
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:53,731
If you wanna face him off,
it might be better to pick another day.

186
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:54,732
What?

187
00:12:54,815 --> 00:12:58,068
See? It's about to get dark.

188
00:12:58,152 --> 00:13:00,488
If you end up fighting in the dark,

189
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:05,201
we won't get a clear view
of all the swollen, beat-up faces.

190
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:07,244
Right, Othello-kun?

191
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:10,414
How do you plan to look
at your own face here?

192
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:14,460
Huh? Everyone here know each other?

193
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:16,670
In that case, Ume-chan...

194
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:18,964
Why don't we all go at it?

195
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,717
Oh, I don't mean doing a brawl.

196
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,803
But we can all face off against
each other, one-on-one, in turn!

197
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:27,223
Like a festival! It'll be fun!

198
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:30,851
Oh, like a kendo team match?

199
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:31,936
Sounds fun.

200
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:33,521
I know, right?

201
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,648
-While we're at it...
-Nice! Nice!

202
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:38,526
-We should invite them to our...
-Yay! Yay!

203
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:39,902
Let me finish, okay?

204
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:42,196
Then the matches will be...

205
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:43,656
Choji and...

206
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:45,282
Umemiya.

207
00:13:46,742 --> 00:13:49,662
Me... and Othello-kun.

208
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:50,663
It's Sakura.

209
00:13:50,746 --> 00:13:53,123
Let me beat that long mop over there.

210
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:57,169
I'll take that eyepatch guy, then.

211
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,797
Aww, a cutey chose me!

212
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:03,259
Hey! If we're facing off,
we don't need to get others involved.

213
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:06,804
But it's more fun if everyone joins in!

214
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:08,430
We...

215
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:10,766
would prefer it that way, too.

216
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,227
See?

217
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:16,605
Jeez, the first years
this time around are handful.

218
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:20,568
May I join, too?

219
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:23,654
I want to fight Hiragi-san.

220
00:14:23,737 --> 00:14:24,864
KOTA SAKO

221
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:27,575
Sako? You...

222
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:31,287
Sorry, Umemiya.

223
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:33,789
I'm in.

224
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:41,088
All right, then it's decided!

225
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:43,591
In the name of our teams...

226
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:49,805
let's all have fun and duke it out!

227
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:06,655
Is it okay for me to be here?

228
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:07,740
Of course.

229
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:11,911
Crap, crap, crap! We're screwed!

230
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:13,871
We're totally screwed!

231
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:15,789
Shut your yappin'.

232
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:19,251
Whose fault do you think it is?

233
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:22,630
There's no point crying about it now.

234
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:26,550
Fill yourself up. It should calm you down.

235
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:28,928
You don't understand at all, Kotoha-san!

236
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:33,307
If... If... If tomorrow...

237
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:36,685
Umemiya-san ends up losing
to that Choji Tomiyama guy...

238
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:42,775
Bofurin will be taken over by Shishitoren.

239
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:45,361
Bofurin might just disappear!

240
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:49,323
But still, crying about it
won't change a thing.

241
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,367
It'll be fine.

242
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:55,162
You already know that those guys
aren't that weak, don't you?

243
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:04,672
I'm done eating. Can I go home now?

244
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:05,673
Whoa, so fast!

245
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:07,341
Oh, you left your veggies.

246
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:10,719
But Umemiya-san and the others
aren't here yet.

247
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:12,471
They're taking forever.

248
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:15,224
They told us to wait,
but they aren't coming.

249
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:19,895
Well, I bet it'll be a lot of work
to calm all those other guys.

250
00:16:20,562 --> 00:16:21,689
But, still...

251
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:24,733
Umemiya said we'd all
go out for a meal, right?

252
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:25,901
But why are we here?

253
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,445
You say that after you
gobbled up Omelet rice?

254
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:33,659
This place is well-known as
the usual hangout spot for Bofurin.

255
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:36,245
I heard they'd gather here before a fight.

256
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:37,788
More importantly...

257
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:40,499
Ko...

258
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:41,625
to...

259
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:42,710
ha!

260
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:47,881
Your hair looks so cute today!
It suits you well!

261
00:16:47,965 --> 00:16:49,049
Is that so?

262
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:52,386
Oh, right! Remember that seedling
I talked about the other day?

263
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:54,471
It has gotten so big!

264
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,640
I'll send it here once summer hits!

265
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:58,350
I'll look forward to that.

266
00:16:58,434 --> 00:16:59,852
What's up with that?

267
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:03,022
As you can see, he really likes her.

268
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:06,817
What? Is she his girlfriend?

269
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,986
Oh, you take it that way?

270
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:10,279
No, I'm not!

271
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,656
Good grief. Don't be stupid.

272
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,533
Yeah! Don't be stupid!

273
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:16,785
What do you take her for?

274
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:17,703
TA-DA

275
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:20,289
-She's my little sister!
-That's not true either!

276
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:22,541
What does he mean?

277
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:30,132
We were raised in the same orphanage.

278
00:17:30,215 --> 00:17:32,551
And he just calls me that on his own.

279
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:34,887
Oh...

280
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:36,722
That's all?

281
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:43,729
Hold up...

282
00:17:43,812 --> 00:17:46,482
-Little sister? Not big sister?
-Yeah.

283
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:47,816
How old are you?

284
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,693
Sixteen. The same as you.

285
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:52,863
You liar! You look
way too old for sixteen!

286
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:55,074
No matter how you cut it,
you're over twe...

287
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:58,952
That was dangerous!
What the hell are you doing?

288
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:00,537
That's right...

289
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:05,459
Kotoha is very mature.

290
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:11,507
Goodness, Sugishita!
Don't go tossing things around like that.

291
00:18:13,383 --> 00:18:16,220
Umemiya dotes on Kotoha-chan a lot.

292
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:20,307
<i>If he finds out</i> that Kotoha-chan
got into any danger...

293
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,060
you know what'll happen, right?

294
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:25,521
Okay.

295
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,065
So good!

296
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:31,360
Kotoha's omelet rice is
the best in all of Japan!

297
00:18:31,443 --> 00:18:32,903
Just shut up and eat.

298
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:38,909
Huh? You're not eating, Hiragi?

299
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:41,370
No, I...

300
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:45,624
I was thinking about what
Shishitoren was like in the past.

301
00:18:45,707 --> 00:18:49,586
Me too. I think
they've been pretty lame lately.

302
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,589
They were different before?

303
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:55,843
Devotees of power...

304
00:18:56,593 --> 00:19:01,098
<i>Shishitoren was a team that
simply sought strength in fights.</i>

305
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:04,518
They are a lot of hotheads
there, yeah, but...

306
00:19:04,601 --> 00:19:07,896
they were never a team that would
chase around some middle school kid.

307
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:12,109
<i>There was one time when
we had an all-out clash with them.</i>

308
00:19:12,609 --> 00:19:14,111
<i>It was a fierce brawl,</i>

309
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:17,364
<i>but it was a feel-good fight.</i>

310
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:19,366
<i>But...</i>

311
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:23,579
<i>grisly rumors began to spread
ever since Tomiyama became their leader.</i>

312
00:19:24,621 --> 00:19:26,874
<i>What happened today wasn't anything new.</i>

313
00:19:26,957 --> 00:19:31,378
<i>I've heard a ton of stories about
how they'd force their way into a fight.</i>

314
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:33,672
<i>Both Tomiyama and Togame...</i>

315
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:36,550
<i>were like symbols
of their devotion to power,</i>

316
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,802
<i>who cared about their team the most...</i>

317
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,222
Just how did things change so much?

318
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:47,519
Well, it all probably changed
because of Tomiyama.

319
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:49,980
Because of him? How exactly?

320
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:51,899
I don't know much myself.

321
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:55,861
But we'll get it when
we talk to them tomorrow.

322
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:59,740
Talk to them?
But we're going to fight them, aren't we?

323
00:19:59,823 --> 00:20:00,782
No, no.

324
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:03,869
Fighting is a type of
communication, Sakura-kun.

325
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:09,416
<i>Sometimes, fists serve as a language that
allows you to understand your opponent.</i>

326
00:20:09,499 --> 00:20:12,419
<i>But well, it's a language that
only we know how to speak.</i>

327
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:16,006
Kotoha, seconds please!

328
00:20:16,089 --> 00:20:19,009
It's way past the time
for the last orders.

329
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:20,219
CAFÉ POTHOS

330
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:23,805
All right, guys! Don't be late tomorrow!

331
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:26,892
{\an8}Kotoha! I'll come again!

332
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:30,604
Everyone!

333
00:20:31,521 --> 00:20:33,857
I never got the chance
to tell you all, so...

334
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:37,110
Thank you so much for saving me!

335
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:39,988
I wish you luck on your fight tomorrow!

336
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:42,491
Yeah!

337
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,368
Don't you worry. We'll be fine.

338
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:46,495
We'll give it our best.

339
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:49,122
It's not like we're fighting for your sa...

340
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:50,707
You're a real idiot.

341
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,920
All you gotta say is,
"You can leave it to us."

342
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:59,341
Just leave the rest
to your big brothers here!

343
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:03,095
Leave it to us...

344
00:21:03,887 --> 00:21:05,097
Good!

345
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:07,766
{\an8}Sakura-san, your face is bright red.

346
00:21:07,849 --> 00:21:08,976
{\an8}Shut up!

347
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,438
<i>Fighting is communication...</i>

348
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:14,982
<i>Fists are a language.</i>

349
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:18,485
<i>I never thought of it that way.</i>

350
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:27,661
All right, now then...

351
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:29,454
Let's go!

352
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:32,624
<i>I've never...</i>

353
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:35,752
<i>gone into a fight for someone else's sake.</i>

354
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:38,338
<i>But...</i>

355
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:40,257
<i>although I'm not sure why...</i>

356
00:21:41,466 --> 00:21:44,011
<i>I feel more invincible than ever before.</i>

357
00:21:48,557 --> 00:21:50,267
Ume-chan!

358
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:52,936
Welcome to our turf!

359
00:21:53,603 --> 00:21:54,688
Yo.

360
00:21:55,605 --> 00:21:57,024
Thanks for having us.

361
00:23:31,618 --> 00:23:36,414
Sakura-san, I had my suspicion,
but do you hate vegetables?

362
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:39,501
What? You got a problem with it?

363
00:23:39,584 --> 00:23:43,255
It's not like I'll have any problem
by not eating them.

364
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:47,217
But since our boss Umemiya-san
is raising vegetables,

365
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:50,720
maybe vegetables are
his source of strength?

366
00:23:51,221 --> 00:23:52,472
So you're saying...

367
00:23:52,556 --> 00:23:55,934
I'm weak because I don't eat
my vegetables?

368
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:57,936
No! Of course not!

369
00:23:58,019 --> 00:23:59,896
That's it! I'm taking you down!

